Conversion_of_anthro_aerosol_emissions_to_forcing=
	-1.325
	~	(W / m2) / (GtAAe / yr)
	~	calibrated from knowing emissions and their radiative forcing
	|

Conversion_of_volcanic_aerosol_emissions_to_CO2_emissions_GtC_pr_VAE=
	2.8
	~	GtC / GtVAe
	~	Numerical values for the volcanic portion of the carbon cycle are \
		generally given as 0.6 GtC pr yr, see eg IPCC AR5 Chapter 6. From 1850 to \
		2007, for which I have volcanic emission data this amounts to 95 GtC. This \
		then is calibrated value to generate cumulative emissions of 95 GtC \
		between 1850 and 2007
	|

Conversion_of_volcanic_aerosol_forcing_to_volcanic_aerosol_emissions=
	-1
	~	(W/m2) / (GtVAe/yr)
	~		|

Conversion_ymoles_per_kg_to_pCO2_yatm=
	0.127044
	~	ppm /(ymoles / litre)
	~	read off (eyeballed) from Fig 3 of Rödenbeck et al 2013 Global \
		surface-ocean pC=2 and sea air CO2 flux variability from an observation \
		driven ocean mixed layer scheme should be 285/2240 (285 is CO2 ppm atm in \
		1850, 2240 is CConcentration ymoles per litre in 1850) is actually a tiny \
		bit less to generate a flow of 0.1779 GtC from atm to ocean for \
		equilibrium conditions
	|

