	~	1
	~		|

CH4_emi_from_agriculture[region]=
	MAX(0, CH4_emi_from_agriculture_a[region] * LN(Red_meat_production[region] / UNIT_conv_Mtrmeat\
		)+CH4_emi_from_agriculture_b[region])
	~	MtCH4/Year
	~	History Source: calculated from \
		https://www.pik-potsdam.de/paris-reality-check/primap-hist/
		This is an example of how correlations get you into trouble: While in the \
		past the correlation between red meat production and CH4 emissions was \
		excellent, if you enter into a world where red meat is no longer produced \
		from animals but from labs, the correlation goes haywire. If you have a \
		better idea, let us know, or better yet, implement your solution!
	|

