fa_to_c[region]=
	MIN ( Max_forest_cut_after_policy[region], MIN ( Forest_land[region], MAX ( 0 , Cropland_gap\
		[region]) ) * Fraction_of_cropland_gap_closed_by_cutting_forests[region])
	~	Mha/y
	~	First (MIN) you cannot use more land for cropland than you have forest land, and \
		second (MAX) you only want to develop cropland if need > actual i.e. gap > \
		0
		Finally, all is embedded in another MIN function in case there is a policy \
		in place to stop forest cutting.
