mort_80_to_84_adjust_factor[region]=
	0.8, 1.3, 1, 1.2, 1.8, 1.4, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 1.8
	~	Dmnl
	~	The correlation between GDPpp and mortality gets weaker at the end of a \
		person's lifetime. Hence the correlation curve has been adjusted by \
		calibrating to the size of the cohort's historical data, assuming that \
		levels (i.e. people in a given age cohort) are more reliably reported by \
		the UN than rates. GET XLS CONSTANTS('e4a-exo.xlsx', 'para' , 'c159' )
	|

